Source: raspberrypi-support
Section: misc
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Eugenio Paolantonio (g7) <me@medesimo.eu>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 8.0.0)
Standards-Version: 3.9.3.1
Homepage: http://raspberrypi.org
Vcs-Git: git://github.com/semplice/raspberrypi-support.git
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/semplice/raspberrypi-support/tree/debian

Package: firmware-raspberrypi
Section: non-free/kernel
Architecture: armel
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Raspberry Pi support files -- firmwares
 This package contains the firmwares required to boot the
 Raspberry Pi(TM).
 .
 It ships the files to /boot, thus requiring the first
 partition of the SD Card mounted to that directory.

Package: linux-image-raspberrypi
Section: kernel
Architecture: armel
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Linux for the Raspberry Pi
 This package contains the Linux kernel and its relative modules
 for the Raspberry Pi(TM).
 .
 It ships some of the files to /boot, thus requiring the first
 partition of the SD Card mounted to that directory.

Package: linux-image-raspberrypi-cutdown
Section: kernel
Architecture: armel
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Conflicts: linux-image-raspberrypi
Description: Cutdown Linux for the Raspberry Pi
 This package contains the Cutdown Linux kernel and its relative modules
 for the Raspberry Pi(TM).
 .
 It ships some of the files to /boot, thus requiring the first
 partition of the SD Card mounted to that directory.

Package: omxil-broadcom-doc
Section: non-free/doc
Architecture: all
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Broadcom Openmax IL implementation documentation
 This package contains the Openmax IL documentation, in HTML.
 .
 See /usr/share/doc/omxil-doc/ilcomponents/index.html for details.

Package: videocore-libraries
Section: non-free/libs
Architecture: armel
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Raspberry Pi support files -- VideoCoreIV libraries
 This package contains the userspace libraries needed
 to get the VideoCoreIV working.
